melesio "mel" casas (november 24, 1929 – october 9, 2002) was an american composer, pianist and music educator. casas was born in san francisco, california, and studied at the university of california, berkeley with darius milhaud and arnold schoenberg. after serving in the us air force during the korean war, he studied at the state university of new york at buffalo with milton babbitt. he then taught at several universities in the united states before settling in europe in 1969. casas's compositions include orchestral works, chamber music, choral works, and solo piano pieces. his works have been performed by the
amrita vidyalayams are a group of cbse affiliated schools in india, providing education from kindergarten to 12th grade. amrita vidyalayams were started by sarada devi in 1949 as a kindergarten in bengaluru, karnataka. today there are over 600 amrita vidyalayams in india. amrita vidyalayams are unique in that they provide education from kindergarten to 12th grade and also offer vocational training in a number of fields. the schools are affiliated with the central board of secondary education (cbse), and offer a uniform curriculum that is based on the indian system of education. the schools are also known for their sporting
in norse mythology (a subset of germanic mythology), elli is a goddess associated with light, beauty, and the moon. elli is also the goddess of the dawn and one of the three valkyries. the name elli has two possible origins. the first is that it may be derived from the verb elli, meaning "to come," "to arrive," or "to appear." the second possible origin is that it may be derived from the noun ell, meaning "a measure of land equal to 120 hides." elli was also known as the goddess of love and fertility. she was often depicted as a
gwendolyn b. bennett (july 8, 1902 – december 12, 1968) was an american politician who served as the 29th mayor of philadelphia from 1951 to 1955 and as a united states senator from pennsylvania from 1955 to 1959. bennett was born in philadelphia, the daughter of bessie louise (née pyle) and james c. bennett. she graduated from the university of pennsylvania in 1922, where she was a member of the alpha chi omega sorority. after college, bennett worked as a secretary for several years in her father's law firm. in 1930, bennett married joseph h. laughlin, with whom she had
two children. after his death in 1942, bennett married william greenough martin in 1945. she had one more child before her death from cancer in 1968 at the age of 73. bennett's political career began in 1934 when she was appointed to the city planning commission. in 1941, she was elected to the philadelphia city council, where she served until 1951. in 1951, bennett was elected mayor of philadelphia, defeating incumbent james kennon by a wide margin. during her time as mayor, bennett implemented many progressive policies including creating a municipal housing authority and creating the city's first public transportation
helena krasowska (b. 1973) polish linguist, professor of the department of slavic languages and literatures at the university of illinois at urbana champaign. she specializes in the syntax and semantics of polish, as well as lexicography, grammar and stylistics. helena krasowska was born in 1973 in warsaw, poland. she received her undergraduate degree from the university of warsaw in 1996, and her graduate degree from the academy of fine arts in warsaw in 2002. krasowska began her academic career at the university of warsaw, where she was a research associate from 2002 to 2004. she then moved to the university
vice admiral helge hjalmar immanuel strömbäck (26 october 1923 – 8 december 2019) was a swedish naval officer and politician who served as the 18th prime minister of sweden from 9 october 1969 to 30 september 1970. strömbäck was born in stockholm, sweden, the son of major hjalmar immanuel strömbäck and his wife gertrud johanna albinia von sydow. he joined the swedish navy in 1943 and retired in 1972 with the rank of vice admiral. he was elected to the riksdag of sweden in 1958 and served as minister for defence from 1959 to 1962. he was chairman of the
meta kristine hansen (1865–1941) was a danish painter, sculptor and graphic artist. meta hansen was born on october 1, 1865 in copenhagen, denmark to the sculptor jacob hansen (1820-1892) and his wife karen møller (1827-1901). hansen studied at the royal danish academy of fine arts from 1883 to 1886 under the guidance of christoffer wilhelm eckersberg and christian krohg. in 1890, she married the sculptor vilhelm hammershøi (1860-1936). the couple had two children, birthe (1891-1976) and hans (1893-1963). hansen is best known for her paintings and sculptures of women, often portraying them as archetypes or allegories. her paintings are often
paul newsome is a gold selling musician, songwriter and record producer who has been active in the music industry since the early 1980s. he has written and produced songs for a variety of artists, including whitney houston, mariah carey, celine dion and aretha franklin. newsome was born in detroit, michigan, united states on june 12th, 1960. he began his musical career playing keyboards in local bands before moving to los angeles to pursue a career in music. in the early 1980s, he began working as a record producer and songwriter, penning tracks for artists such as whitney houston, mariah carey,
the phare de l'espiguette (espiguette lighthouse) is an active lighthouse located on the tip of the pointe de l'espiguette, on the french island of corsica. the lighthouse was built in 1892 and is operated by the french national park service. the pointe de l'espiguette is a popular tourist destination, due to its striking natural features and its close proximity to the city of ajaccio. the lighthouse is situated on a promontory at the tip of the point and is visible from a great distance. the phare de l'espiguette was built in 1892 as part of a project to improve navigation
jack reynor (born 23 january 1992) is an irish actor. he is known for his roles in the irish films the young offenders (2013), the revenant (2015), and brooklyn (2015). reynor was born in dublin, ireland, the son of derry native gerry (née o'brien) and australian actress deborah reynor. his maternal grandparents were irish and scottish. reynor has two older sisters. he attended st columba's college, dublin. reynor started his acting career at the age of fourteen, appearing in a school production of peter pan. in 2006, reynor appeared in the short film the cat and the canary, which won
the academy award for best live action short film at the 78th academy awards. in 2007, he appeared in the irish television series fair city as brendan dillon, a role he reprised in two further appearances over the next two years. reynor also appeared in the short film terminal velocity alongside tom hardy and michael fassbender. in 2009, he appeared in the irish feature film the guard which was directed by john michael mcdonagh. in 2010, he starred as gary cooper's son scotty in the irish feature film whiskey tango foxtrot. reynor had his first leading role as conor mcloughlin
clashes between pro-maidan and anti-maidan demonstrators erupted in odessa, ukraine on may 2, 2014. the violence began when pro-maidan demonstrators marched towards the city center to demand the resignation of governor sergiy taruta and alleged election fraud. anti-maidan demonstrators, who were mainly elderly residents of odessa and its suburbs, formed a human chain to block the pro-maidan march. the confrontation turned violent, with both sides throwing stones and molotov cocktails at each other. by the end of the day, at least two people had been killed and dozens injured. the clashes continued sporadically for several more days until may 6
bruce elliot tapper (born in the united states on july 26, 1963) is an american journalist, who currently serves as the chief political correspondent for cnn. his reporting has focused primarily on u.s. politics and national security issues. tapper was born in washington, d.c., the son of barbara (née elliot), a homemaker, and bruce tapper, a naval officer and lawyer. he was raised in bethesda, maryland, where he attended the private bethesda-chevy chase school and played varsity tennis and football. he then attended duke university, where he received a b.a. in political science in 1985. after graduating from duke, tapper
began his career as a staffer for then-rep. jay dickey (r-ar) before moving to the capitol hill bureau of the "washington times" in 1987. in 1989, he joined cnn as a correspondent. in 1993, he became the network's congressional correspondent and in 1997 he became the chief washington correspondent, a position he held until his departure from cnn in early 2013. tapper has received numerous honors during his career, including two george polk awards for investigative reporting (in 2002 and 2006), an alfred i. dupont-columbia university silver baton award for excellence in broadcast journalism (2002), a george foster peabody award
severe tropical cyclone ron was the strongest tropical cyclone on record to form in the southern hemisphere, with peak wind speeds of 260 km/h (160 mph) . the system formed on october 10 near the coast of western australia and rapidly intensified into a category 5 hurricane on october 13. it quickly moved across the indian ocean, reaching a peak intensity of 330 km/h (205 mph) before making landfall on the andaman islands on october 16. ron rapidly weakened over land and dissipated on october 18. ron was one of the deadliest tropical cyclones in australian history, killing at least
be the cowboy is the fifth studio album by american country music artist craig morgan. it was released on october 6, 2012, through mercury nashville. the album was produced by morgan and ashley gorley. "be the cowboy" is a return to form for morgan, who has been working on new material for the album for the past two years. he says of the album, "i wanted to make an album that showed off my vocal range and that was really fun to record. i think the fans are going to love it." the album's first single, "that's what i do",
air vice marshal robert stewart blucke, cb, dso, afc (13 october 1893 – 10 january 1966) was a senior officer in the royal air force. born in 1893, blucke entered the royal military academy, sandhurst, in 1912 and was commissioned into the royal air force on 15 november 1914. he served during world war i as a pilot in the royal flying corps and later as a staff officer at the air ministry. after the war he attended the imperial defence college and became commanding officer of no. 249 squadron raf in 1938. during world war ii he commanded no.
craig noel (august 25, 1915 – april 3, 1984) was an american singer, songwriter and actor. he was known as the lead singer of the pop and rock band noel, which he formed in 1941. noel was born in whitefish bay, wisconsin, to irish immigrants. after serving in world war ii, he moved to los angeles and began a successful music career. he released several successful albums and singles throughout the 1950s and 1960s, including "the wanderer" (1956), "here comes the sun" (1962), and "the last great american dream" (1970). he also starred in several movies, including "the hudsucker proxy"
the leica sl2 is a full-frame mirrorless camera that was announced by leica on october 10, 2012. it is the successor to the leica m10 and has a resolution of 24 megapixel. the camera body is made of magnesium alloy and has a total weight of only 1,340 g. the leica sl2 has a number of new features and improvements over its predecessor, the leica m10. these include a new sensor with more than double the number of effective pixels (24 megapixels vs 8 megapixels), an updated processor, and a faster lens mount. the camera can also capture 4k ultra
the tandy 2000 is a personal computer released by tandy corporation in 1982. it was one of the first mass-produced computers with a graphical user interface, and was essentially a commodore pet with an improved rom, memory, and i/o. the tandy 2000 was a relatively early adopter of the graphical user interface, and was one of the first computers to ship with a mouse. the tandy 2000 also had a number of innovative features, including two floppy disk drives and support for high-resolution graphics. the tandy 2000 was moderately successful, although it lacked the market share of more popular computers
phacelia insularis, the coast phacelia is a perennial plant found on the coasts of north america and europe. it is a member of the sunflower family, and is closely related to phacelia tanacetifolia and phacelia distans. the coast phacelia is a herbaceous plant that typically grows to a height of 1-2 feet, but can reach up to 4 feet in height. it has narrow, lance-shaped leaves that are green on the upper surface and white on the lower surface. the flowers are yellow or orange, and are arranged in clusters at the top of the stem. the coast phacelia is
