cabot's tern (thalasseus acuflavidus) is a small seabird in the sterna genus. it is found in the north atlantic and north pacific. the cabot's tern is a small tern, measuring 23–27 cm in length and weighing around 0.75 kg. plumage is a light grayish-white, with a black cap and black band across the chest. the underparts are white, with a black breast band. the legs and bill are also black. the cabot's tern is found in the north atlantic and north pacific, where it breeds on coastal islands and coasts. it feeds on small fish, crustaceans, and marine invertebrates. it
