the 2/26th battalion was an infantry battalion of the australian imperial force raised in victoria in 1916. the battalion was deployed to the western front and fought in the battle of the somme, the third battle of ypres, and the battle of passchendaele. after the war, the battalion was disbanded and its members returned to civilian life. the 2/26th battalion was raised at echuca on 2/26th february 1916 under the command of lieutenant colonel t.b.l. howes. the battalion was composed of men from rural victoria and consisted of three rifle companies – a, b, and c – and a machine
gun company. the battalion sailed for europe on 9th april 1916 and arrived in france on 25th may. the 2/26th battalion first saw action at the battle of the somme on 1st july 1916 where it fought in the front line alongside the 1st australian division. the battalion suffered heavy casualties, including 27 killed and 180 wounded. the next day, it attacked bois francais and secured its objectives despite heavy casualties. over the next few weeks, the battalion fought in several engagements including flers–courcelette, le sars, thiepval ridge, pozières, mouquet farm and morlancourt. by the end of august 1916, it
independent studio services or iss is a company that specializes in providing various audio, video, and production services to independent filmmakers, video game developers, and other media producers. independent studio services was founded in 2002 by jason fried and david heinemeier hansson. fried and hansson had both worked at software company apple inc. where they pioneered the use of the internet for product development. after leaving apple, fried and hansson started a web development company called 37signals. iss offers a variety of services including audio production, video production, post-production, and marketing services. services are offered in both metropolitan areas and
dome village was a self-governing community of about 1,000 people who lived in domes on the moon during the 1970s and 1980s. dome village was founded in 1973 by gerard k. o'neill, who was then an engineer at the jet propulsion laboratory. o'neill envisioned a society of self-sufficient, space-faring individuals who would live in environmentally friendly domes on the moon. dome village was one of the first attempts to establish a permanent human settlement on the moon. the community lasted for about 20 years, until 1985. at its peak, dome village had a population of about 1,000 people. however, due
cult of static is the sixth studio album by british rock band muse. it was released on 10 october 2017 through atlantic records. the album was produced by the band and longtime collaborator paul epworth. it is muse's first studio album in eight years and the first since the 2nd law (2009) not to be nominated for a grammy award. the album has received generally positive reviews from music critics, who praised its production and muse's experimentation with their sound. it debuted at number one on the uk albums chart and reached the top five in countries including australia, canada,
and the united states. in an interview with "nme", frontman matt bellamy said of the album: "i think it’s our most diverse record musically, sonically and lyrically. we’ve been writing songs for two years now and i think it’s really come together." muse formed in 1994 in teignmouth, devon, england. the band released their debut studio album showbiz (1996) which gained them a following in the uk and europe. their second album, absolution (1998), peaked at number two on the uk albums chart and spawned four singles, including "hysteria" which became their first number one single in the uk. the
ancestral sequence reconstruction (asr) – also known as phylogenetic reconstruction or genealogical reconstruction – is the process of reconstructing the ancestral sequence of a given population or species. asr can be used to study phylogenetic relationships and to infer the evolutionary history of a population or species. asr is an important tool for biologists, geneticists, and other researchers who study populations and species. asr can be used to study the evolution of populations, genes, and traits; to understand how populations change over time; and to identify the sources of genetic variation in a population. asr is based on the assumption
that we can reconstruct the ancestral sequence of a population or species by analyzing the sequence of nucleotides (or proteins) present in the genomes of representatives from that population or species. the ancestral sequence can be determined by tracing the evolutionary history of specific gene copies in the population or species. asr is a relatively recent technique, which has been developed over the past several decades. today, there are several different methods for asr, which can be divided into three main categories: direct methods, indirect methods, and reconstruction methods. direct methods include whole-genome sequencing (wgs) and next-generation sequencing (ngs). wgs
