norman osborn is a fictional character appearing in american comic books published by marvel comics. the character is a costumed supervillain who is the archenemy of spider-man. norman osborn was created by stan lee and steve ditko, and first appeared in the amazing spider-man #15 (august 1962). osborn is the son of harry osborn, a wealthy industrialist, and his wife, mary. harry osborn is killed in a lab accident when norman was young and norman is raised by his aunt and uncle. norman becomes resentful of his aunt because she spoils him and does not show him the same level
