the huaiyin–huai'an campaign (两淮战役) was a campaign fought by the national revolutionary army (nra) of the republic of china from september 18, 1937 to november 15, 1937 against the japanese invaders during world war ii. the nra was composed of soldiers from both nationalist and communist parties. the huaiyin–huai'an campaign was a major battle fought just south of shanghai, with the nra eventually retreating northward across the yangtze river into jiangsu province. the campaign saw fierce fighting in northern huaiyin and huai'an prefectures, as well as in shanghai itself. the eventual outcome was a japanese victory, which resulted in the
