marvin leroy keyes (february 18, 1947 – november 2, 1988) was an american murderer and serial killer. keyes was born in wichita, kansas, to harold and florence (née leroy) keyes. he had two sisters, shirley and betty. in 1965, keyes enlisted in the united states air force and served until 1969. he was discharged due to a psychiatric disorder. in 1974, keyes moved to alaska and began working as a handyman and carpenter. he met and married doreen barlow in 1976; the couple had one child. in 1980, keyes was arrested for armed robbery in anchorage. he was sentenced to
ambedkarite is a section of people who identify with the philosophy of dr. b. r. ambedkar. born in 1891, ambedkar is considered one of the most influential political and social thinkers of the 20th century. he was an advocate for social justice, and his work helped to form the basis for the indian constitution. ambedkarite beliefs focus on the idea that every individual is deserving of equal rights and opportunities, regardless of their race or caste. they believe that all people should be able to lead healthy, fulfilling lives, free from discrimination and oppression. ambedkarite communities exist all over the
polly is a 1989 american made-for-television musical comedy film directed by les mayfield and produced by robert simonds. the screenplay is by lowell ganz and babaloo mandel. the film tells the story of pollyanna (pamela reed), an unassuming girl who is determined to follow her dreams of becoming a singer despite the disapproval of her overbearing and judgmental mother (jean stapleton). pollyanna forms a singing group with her friends, and they journey to various cities in search of success. along the way, they are faced with obstacles such as poor reviews, ridicule from audiences, and personal conflicts. however, they persevere
shay patrick cormac is a fictional character and the protagonist in the novel series, "the stand." cormac is a modified irish setter who is immune to the common cold and has an extraordinary sense of smell. he is employed by the government as a bloodhound and specializes in tracking down diseased animals. cormac is also a member of the "church of jesus christ of latter-day saints" and is called to serve a two-year mission in england. cormac was born on november 9, 1958, in county monaghan, ireland. he was adopted by american parents and moved to the united states when
he was two years old. cormac attended brigham young university on a basketball scholarship and played for the university's varsity team for three seasons. after graduating from college, cormac worked as a bouncer and bodyguard before being hired by the government as a bloodhound. cormac first appeared in stephen king's novel, "the stand," in 1978. the novel tells the story of a pandemic that causes the majority of the human population to become sick and die; cormac is one of only a few people who are immune to the disease. cormac travels around the united states tracking down diseased animals
youthquake is the second album by the american rock band linkin park, released on september 23, 2000, through warner bros. records. it is the band's first album with vocalist chester bennington and was produced by the band's mike shinoda and rick rubin. the album has been described as nu metal, while also incorporating influences from other genres such as rap metal, alternative rock, and pop. its songs are primarily driven by bennington's emotionally charged vocals and aggressive lyrics, which have been compared to those of early grunge pioneers like kurt cobain and eddie vedder. "youthquake" has been cited as a
major influence by several popular contemporary rock bands. the album was well-received by critics, who praised its new sound and bennington's vocals. it debuted at number one on the us "billboard" 200 chart, selling over 267,000 copies in its first week. the album has since sold over 2 million copies in the united states. "youthquake" has also been commercially successful elsewhere, topping the charts in countries including australia, canada, ireland, new zealand, norway, sweden and switzerland. linkin park released their debut album "hybrid theory" in 2000 to critical acclaim. the band toured extensively in support of the album and gained
alto mail was a multi-service email client for the iphone and ipad that was released in december 2010. the app was developed by mailchimp, who also released an email client for the iphone called mail. alto mail is a multipurpose email client for ios devices that includes features common to many of the applications on the app store, such as push notifications, inline images, and unified inboxes. the app was designed to be simple and efficient with a focus on productivity, allowing users to focus on their email rather than spend time trying to figure out how to use the
yusuf gowon (born yusuf mogi in 1936) was the president of nigeria from 1966 to 1970 and from 1975 to 1979. he was also the chairman of the national party from 1978 to 1979. gowon was a military general and a key figure in nigerian independence. gowon was born on 22 february 1936 in bagamoyo, tanganyika (now tanzania). after attending secondary school in dar es salaam, he attended the royal military academy sandhurst in england, receiving his commission as a second lieutenant in the nigerian army in 1953. after serving with the 2nd battalion, nigerian regiment (2nir), gowon became a
company commander in the 3rd battalion, nigerian regiment (3nir) during the biafra war of independence. gowon also served as an intelligence officer with the british military administration in nigeria (bafn) during the early 1960s. gowon played an instrumental role in nigeria's independence from british rule, serving as minister of defence from 1963 to 1966 and as minister of information from 1965 to 1966. he also served as chairman of the joint chiefs of staff from 1965 to 1966. in 1966, gowon was elected president of nigeria, defeating incumbent chief obafemi awolowo in a fiercely contested election. as president, gowon oversaw
u.n.l.v. is a hip-hop group from new york city, formed in 1993. the group's style has been described as "hybrid punk" and "thug rap". u.n.l.v. was formed in 1993 by rapper mf doom, producer madlib, and dj premier. the group's original lineup consisted of doom, premier, kool keith, and vinnie paz. the group's debut album, united nationals, was released in 1994 and featured the singles "hey mf doom" and "united national anthem". the album was largely ignored by mainstream audiences but has since been praised by hip-hop critics. u.n.l.v.'s second album, 1995's united we stand, was more commercially successful than
a term used in shi'i terminology, "hujja" denotes the divine quality of imam al-mahdi and his future role. "hujjat" is the arabic word for "signs" or "proofs" of this divine quality. the shi'i muslims believe that the mahdi, who is also known as the hidden imam, will appear at some point in time in order to restore justice and righteousness to the world. they believe that he possesses all of the qualities of a perfect prophet, and that his coming will be marked by many signs and indications. the term "hujja" refers to these signs/proofs, and is used to describe
wendell cox is an american urban policy expert and public speaker. he is the founder and president of the wendell cox institute, a think tank based in oakland, california. cox has written extensively on urban policy, state and local government, transportation, housing, and economics. he is also a regular commentator on national television and radio programs. cox was born in chicago, illinois in 1939. he received his undergraduate degree from the university of chicago in 1961 and his m.p.p. from harvard university in 1966. from 1966 to 1971 he served as a staff member of the u.s. house of representatives
committee on public works. from 1971 to 1976 he was a senior research associate at the national bureau of economic research, where he co-authored the influential book the structure of local economic activity (1976). in 1976 cox founded the wendell cox institute, which is based in oakland, california. the institute's mission is "to promote informed public policymaking through research and education on urban issues." the institute conducts research on a variety of topics related to urban policy, including transportation, housing, economics, demographics, and climate change. it also publishes reports and studies on these topics. cox has spoken at numerous national
melton is a suburb in metropolitan melbourne, australia, located in the north-west of the city. at the 2016 census, melton had a population of 18,801. melton was established in the late 1880s and originally consisted of a small number of scattered farmhouses and businesses. the area began to grow rapidly in the 1920s and 1930s with the arrival of new families and businesses, as well as the development of local schools and sporting clubs. by the 1960s, melton had become a major suburban area with a range of shops, schools, hospitals and recreational facilities. since the late 1990s, melton has
thabo mvuyelwa mbeki (; born 18 june 1942) is a south african politician who served as the 17th president of south africa from 14 december 1999 to 27 may 2008, and was the first black african to hold that office. born in 1942 in umtata, transkei, mbeki was educated at fort hare university and the university of london. after working as a journalist and civil servant, he joined the african national congress (anc) in the late 1960s. he rose through the ranks of the party, becoming its deputy president in 1989 and president in 1999. mbeki's presidency was marked by
tensions with white south africans, a weak economy, and allegations of corruption. in 2007, mbeki was forced to step down after being diagnosed with prostate cancer. he retired from public life in 2008 and died two years later at the age of 78. thabo mbeki was born on 18 june 1942 in umtata, transkei. he attended fort hare university where he earned a b.a. in political science in 1964. mbeki then studied at the university of london where he earned an m.a. in political science in 1965 and a d.phil. in 1970. mbeki began his career as a journalist for
black studies, or africana studies (with nationally recognized variants such as african american studies), is an academic field that investigates the history, experiences, and current realities of people of african descent. the field emerged as a legitimate field of inquiry in the 1960s and 1970s, when scholars and activists began to explore the unique experiences of people of african descent in the united states, africa, and the caribbean. black studies programs have since become an important part of many universities around the world. black studies programs typically emphasize critical thinking and analysis, while also fostering an appreciation for african culture
wizard world chicago comic con, commonly known as wizard world, is a pop culture convention held in chicago, illinois. it was founded by shel dorf in 1971. the first wizard world convention was held in february 1971 at the hilton hotel in chicago. it was called "wizard world of comics." the event featured popular comic-book artists of the time, including gene colan, neal adams, bob kane and jim steranko. dorf also served as the event's promoter and emcee. in 1974, dorf moved wizard world from the hilton hotel to the state fairgrounds in champaign, illinois. the champaign event was renamed
"wizard world of science fiction." that year, attendance at the convention reached 10,000 people. in 1978, wizard world moved to its current location at the mccormick place convention center in chicago. the event was renamed "wizard world of comics & science fiction." that year, attendance reached 20,000 people. in 1984, wizard world became an annually scheduled event. dorf retired as wizard world's promoter in 2002 and handed over management of the convention to his son shel dorf jr. shel dorf jr. remained as ceo until he stepped down in april 2018. since 2002, wizard world has hosted several events outside
unoma ndili okorafor is a nigerian computer scientist and author. she is best known for her novel who fears death, which has been translated into twenty languages and won the arthur c. clarke award and the locus award. okorafor was born in nigeria in 1969. she completed a bachelor's degree in computer science at the university of ibadan in 1992, and a master's degree at the massachusetts institute of technology in 1996. she then worked as a research scientist at microsoft research in redmond, washington, before moving to london in 2002 to work as a software engineer at google. okorafor's
"african flower" or "little african flower" (petite fleur de l'afrique) is a genus of two dozen or so species of flowering plants in the family asteraceae, native to africa. the genus is endemic to the continent, with the majority of its species occurring in west africa. the plants grow in dry habitats, such as open woodland. many are annuals or biennials, growing to a height of 30 cm. the flowers are small, with yellow, pink, or purple petals which may be slightly twisted. there are typically five petals, though some have six. the flowers are pollinated by bees. african flower
amideast (the america-mideast educational and training services) is a not-for-profit organization that helps educators, students and professionals from the united states and jordan to build constructive relationships and share knowledge. amideast was founded in 2003 by dr. eileen o'leary and dr. mona al-masry. the organization is headquartered in amman, jordan with a branch office in washington, d.c. amideast's mission is to help educators, students and professionals from the united states and jordan to build constructive relationships and share knowledge. amideast provides education, training and support to its partners in the united states and jordan on a variety of topics related
to cross-cultural communication, business, arts and humanities. amideast also offers professional development opportunities for american educators in collaboration with their jordanian counterparts. amideast has collaborated with universities in the united states, including georgetown university, the university of maryland baltimore county (umbc) and george washington university (gwu). in addition, amideast has partnerships with several american universities that offer joint degree programs with jordanian universities, including al-azhar university in cairo, egypt; american university of sharjah in the united kingdom; and ain shams university in cairo, egypt. amideast's current focus areas include: arts and culture; business; cross-cultural communication; education; diplomacy; global health; homeland
"finally found" is the debut single of british singer-songwriter james arthur. the song was written by arthur, jesy nelson, and benny blanco and produced by the latter two. it was released on 10 march 2018 by rca records. "finally found" is a ballad about finally finding someone that arthur loved and lost. the song's lyrics talk about how the protagonist has been searching for them all over the world and finally finds them in the end. it received mostly positive reviews from critics, who praised its sentimental lyrics and production. "finally found" peaked at number three on the uk singles
chart and number eight on the us "billboard" hot 100. james arthur was born on 6 may 1998 in london, england. he started singing at an early age and started posting videos of himself singing covers of songs on social media when he was just thirteen years old. after gaining popularity on youtube, arthur signed a recording contract with syco music in 2015 and released his first single "impossible" that year. he followed it up with the single "i don't wanna live forever (fifty shades darker)" in 2016 which became his first number-one single in the uk. in 2017, arthur
the south bank lion is an 1837 sculpture by the english artist sir john flaxman. the lion is one of the sculptures that make up the monument to the great fire of london. the south bank lion is a colossal bronze sculpture of a lioness, located on the south bank of the river thames in london, england. it is one of a group of sculptures known as the monument to the great fire of london, and was cast in 1837. the monument is designed by sir john flaxman and is made from over 1500kg of bronze. the lioness stands at
a height of 10 metres (33 feet), and her head and front paws are carved from a single block of stone. the statue is located on hungerford bridge, between waterloo bridge and blackfriars bridge, and can be seen from many parts of london. the lioness was originally part of a much larger sculpture, known as the south bank group, which also included statues of a boy child, an infant girl, a horse, a dog, and a monkey. however, due to budgetary constraints, only the lioness and boy child were completed. the statue was badly damaged in world war ii bombing
mindaugas murza (born 16 december 1973), officially known as mindaugas murzas, is a lithuanian professional basketball coach and former player. he is the current head coach of the lithuanian national basketball team. he won a bronze medal with the lithuania national basketball team at the eurobasket 2003. murza was born in klaipėda, lithuania. he played college basketball at iona college, where he was a two-time atlantic 10 conference player of the year. after college, he played in europe for 14 years, including stops with teams in spain, italy, belgium, and germany. in 2003, he helped lithuania win a bronze medal
the battle of kathio, or battle of the river kwai, was fought on 1 may 1942 by allied forces and the japanese imperial army in northeastern thailand. the battle was the first major engagement of world war ii in southeast asia and was a decisive victory for the allies. the battle began with an allied bombing campaign against japanese positions in the area, followed by a land assault by the 22nd indian infantry division. after two days of fighting, the japanese retreated across the kwai river, losing almost 8,000 men in the process. the battle was a significant victory for
awukudae festival (meaning: "wednesday ceremony", is a three-day annual festival held in awukudae, awaji island, hyogo prefecture, japan. the festival is dedicated to the deity of the island, kaneshige-no-mikoto. the awukudae festival is held on the third wednesday of every month from april to october. on the first day of the festival, a procession is made to the island's main shrine, where a number of ceremonies are performed. the second day is devoted to music and dance performances, and on the final day there are market stalls and entertainment programmes. awukudae is one of the most popular tourist destinations in
kamloops lake in british columbia, canada is a large alpine lake that straddles the provincial border between b.c. and alberta. it is located in the kamloops region, about northeast of the city of kamloops. the lake is about long and wide, with a surface area of about . the lake is fed by the north and middle forks of the columbia river, as well as the little columbia river. it is known for its trout fishing and its many mountain resorts, including kamloops lake resort, which has a capacity of 1,500 guests. the lake is also popular for boating, swimming,
eu'vend (official subtitle the international trade fair of electrical, electronic and optical products) is the leading trade fair for electrical, electronic and optical products in the benelux region. the eu'vend trade fair is organised every two years in brussels by the benelux economic union. in 2015, it will take place from 17 to 20 september. the eu'vend trade fair offers exhibitors a unique platform to showcase their products and services to a wide range of buyers from all over europe. more than 4500 companies from over 50 countries are expected to participate in this year's event. the eu'vend trade fair
