the punjab bar council is a statutory body constituted under the punjab legal services authority act, 2008. it is responsible for regulating the legal profession in the state of punjab. the punjab bar council was established on 15 july 2008, pursuant to the punjab legal services authority act, 2008. the purpose of the bar council is to regulate the legal profession in the state of punjab. the bar council has a membership of 66 lawyers, including 33 district bar presidents and 23 chairpersons from various courts in the state. it is also responsible for conducting registrations and examinations for admission
ben moore (born january 2, 1960) is an american composer and musician. moore has composed music for theater, film, and video games. moore was born in huntsville, alabama and began composing music at an early age. he studied music at new york university and the juilliard school of music, graduating with a bachelor of arts in 1985. after graduation, moore moved to los angeles to pursue a career in music. he has since composed music for theater, film, and video games. moore has won numerous awards for his work, including an emmy award for his score for the television series
thinopus is the name given to a genus of extinct marine reptiles that lived during the cretaceous period. the thinopuses were a genus of marine reptiles that lived during the cretaceous period. the members of this genus were small animals, measuring in total only a few inches in length. they had thin, scaly skins and were adapted for life in coastal environments. the thinopuses were a diverse group of animals, with members that lived in both salt water and freshwater environments. some species were capable of diving to great depths, while others were more shore-based. all members of the thinopuses
