nef stadium (officially known as the ali sami nef stadium) is an all-seater stadium in the maltese capital of valletta. the stadium is currently used mostly for football matches and was the home ground of the maltese side valletta f.c. between 1998 and 2014. the stadium has a capacity of around 10,000 people and was built on the site of the former tal-tal stadium which was demolished in 1998. nef stadium was officially opened on 15 september 1998 by then-president of malta, edwin schattner. the match between valletta and hibernian fc was the first game played at the stadium. the
