robinvale is a town on the south-eastern fringe of the greater toronto area, in the regional municipality of york, ontario, canada. the town had a population of 5,689 at the canada 2016 census. robinvale is situated in the fertile plain of the rouge river valley, about east of toronto and north-west of milton keynes in the united kingdom. the town is bisected by highway 401. the town grew up around a railway station and was originally named after a railway official, j.d. robin. in 1875, j.d. robin donated a parcel of land to the grand trunk railway in order to
rocks state park is a public recreation area in central utah, united states. the park is situated on the eastern slopes of the wasatch range, about halfway between salt lake city and park city. the park is popular for hiking, mountain biking, picnicking, and rock climbing. the park has a visitor center, which offers exhibits on geology, history, and wildlife. it also has a campground with 105 campsites, a day-use area with a playground and a picnic area, and a small nature reserve. rocks state park was established in 1974 by the utah state legislature as a result of public
ramón sánchez gómez, better known by his stage name ramón de algeciras (born 8 january 1984), is a spanish singer and songwriter. he achieved commercial success with his second album, 2007's soy un hombre, which spawned the singles "la vida es un sueño" and "besos". in 2009, he won the mtv europe music award for best spanish act. ramón de algeciras was born on 8 january 1984 in gijón, asturias. he started his musical career at the age of 10, when he formed a band with his friends. at the age of 15 he moved to madrid to study music
technology at the conservatory of music. after a year he decided to give up his studies and focus on his music career. in 2004, ramón released his first album, which did not achieve commercial success. in 2007, he released his second album, soy un hombre. the album spawned the singles "la vida es un sueño" and "besos". the following year, he won the mtv europe music award for best spanish act. in 2009, ramón released his third album, donde estás tú. the album spawned the singles "no me quiero ir" and "por amor". in 2013, ramón released his fourth album,
bobo (1951–1968) was a western lowland gorilla who lived at the columbus zoo and aquarium in columbus, ohio from 1951 until his death in 1968. he was one of the first gorillas born in captivity and is considered to be one of the zoo's most famous residents. bobo was born in 1951 at the columbus zoo and aquarium, one of the first gorillas born in captivity. he was a popular attraction for visitors, and his death in 1968 caused a public outcry. he was posthumously inducted into the gorilla hall of fame and has been featured in documentaries and books
maputo international airport , also known as lobito international airport, is the primary international airport of the city of maputo, mozambique. the airport serves as a hub for mozambican airways and is also served by south african airways, tap portugal, and ethiopian airlines. the airport has a total capacity of 5 million passengers per year. the airport was first established in 1949 as a royal air force base. it was later taken over by mozambique airways in 1961 and underwent extensive renovation in the 1990s. the original terminal was replaced with a new facility in 2003 that features an international
alsophila baileyana, synonym cyathea baileyana, also known as bailey's cyathea, bailey's palm, bailey's tree fern, bailey's cyatheca, bailey's tree, is a species of fern in the family cyathecae. it is endemic to the eastern united states. this fern is a medium-sized plant growing to about 10 inches (25 cm) tall. the fronds are bipinnate, with a long petiole and a blade about 3 inches (8 cm) wide. the tips of the fronds are blunt, unlike those of many other members of the genus alsophila, which are pointed. the undersides of the fronds are white and finely ribbed. the sporangia are
a sky villa is a housing concept that was first proposed by architect kenneth frampton in the early 1990s. it is a type of vertical living that consists of stacked apartments that are connected to each other and to the ground by staircases or elevators. the idea behind sky villas is that they would provide a more efficient way to live than traditional housing structures. by living in stacked apartments, people would be able to allocate more space to each individual and would be able to take advantage of open-plan layouts that would allow for a more unified living environment.
damien o'hagan is a former gaelic footballer who played as a left corner-back for the meath senior football team. he is the father of current meath footballer colm o'hagan. damien o'hagan was born in mullingar, county westmeath in 1984. after playing club football for mullingar based club st brigid's, he joined the meath senior team in 2003. o'hagan made his debut for meath in a 2002 national football league game against kildare and played a key role in meath's successive all-ireland senior football championship wins in 2005 and 2006. o'hagan retired from inter-county football following the conclusion of the 2007
giovanni battista buonamente (ca. 1595 – 1642) was an italian painter of the baroque period. born in cremona, buonamente studied under his father, girolamo, before traveling to rome in 1616. there, he entered the studio of bernini, who was to have a significant influence on his later work. he also spent time in the studios of caravaggio and peter paul rubens. in 1627 he returned to cremona, where he remained most of his life. he had several notable pupils, including giuseppe maria crespi and filippo maria lippi. buonamente's paintings are typically solemn and religious in nature, characterized by heavy drapery
in solid mechanics, in the field of thermodynamics, critical speed is the speed of a body or system at which the temperature of the system no longer increases with increasing velocity. critical speed is a fundamental concept in the field of thermodynamics. it is related to the concepts of flow speed, critical pressure, and critical temperature. the critical speed of a body or system is the speed at which the temperature of the system reaches its maximum. this occurs when the heat transfer from the body or system to its environment becomes entirely dissipated. the critical speed of a gas
3 squadron saaf was a squadron of the south african air force. 3 squadron was formed on 1 october 1940 at warmbaths, near kimberley, as a night fighter squadron equipped with the hurricane. on 10 may 1941, 3 squadron moved to walvis bay and began operations as a day fighter squadron equipped with the spitfire mk ii. the squadron operated from walvis bay until it was disbanded on 15 september 1950. 3 squadron was reformed on 1 october 1978 at afb waterkloof as a fighter-bomber squadron equipped with the f-5e tiger ii. the squadron moved to afb bloemfontein in 1983
and converted to the f-16a fighting falcon. the squadron participated in operation reindeer, the south african defence force's contribution to operation restore hope, in somalia in december 1992. the squadron saw combat in operation modular edge in southern angola in 1998 and 1999, during which it destroyed several enemy aircraft and armoured vehicles. in 2000, the squadron moved to afb oudtshoorn to convert back to the f-5e tiger ii. the squadron was again disbanded on 31 march 2003, but was reactivated on 1 october 2006 at afb waterkloof as an airbase defence unit equipped with the sa-330 puma. the unit
balls are a folk art form and considered as one of the most popular toys in japan. the temari is a ball made from cloth, paper or plastic and is often brightly coloured. it is typically about 18 centimeters in diameter and is often decorated with a pattern or a figure. the temari is believed to have originated in china and was brought to japan in the 6th century. the word temari likely comes from the chinese word "tamar" which means "to sweep". the temari was originally used as a toy by children to play with, but it has since
francis chapman grant (1823 – 1889 or 1893) was an american painter. francis chapman grant was born in 1823 in philadelphia, pennsylvania, the eldest of six children of samuel and rebecca chapman grant. his father was a successful merchant and banker. after completing his preparatory studies at the academy of philadelphia, francis began his career as a painter, first working in philadelphia and then traveling to europe. he spent most of his career painting portraits and landscapes in the united states, but also worked in europe. in 1875 he settled in new york city, where he died in 1889 or
specimen ridge, el. is an approximately 2,000-foot-high mountain ridge located in the elk mountains of east-central colorado. the ridge is a dissected anticline that forms a long, narrow crest extending northwest from the headwaters of the south elk river. specimen ridge is the most prominent of a number of conspicuous ridges that form the northern boundary of the elk mountains. specimen ridge is one of several ridges located in east-central colorado that are characterized by high elevations, rugged topography, and dramatic scenery. the ridge is composed of precambrian and cambrian age rock formations that have been heavily eroded over time.
the highest points on the ridge are located near its northeastern end, where the rocks are relatively uniform in composition. near the southern end of the ridge, however, the rock formations are more heavily fractured and are composed of a variety of different geological materials. the ridge is traversed by a number of small streams that originate in the nearby mountains. these streams flow down the slope of specimen ridge before joining larger rivers that flow into the colorado river near utah lake. the streams that flow down the eastern side of specimen ridge are relatively short and shallow, while
massacre day was a holiday in boston, massachusetts, united states which commemorated the 1770 boston massacre. historically, the holiday was celebrated on the anniversary of the event by a public gathering in faneuil hall, where speeches were given and resolutions passed in commemoration. the boston massacre was an event that took place on march 5, 1770, in which a group of british soldiers fired into a crowd of civilians protesting the tea act, killing five people and wounding many more. the event became a rallying cry for the american revolutionaries, and has been described as one of the most important
william henry anderson (21 april 1882 – 9 may 1969) was an english author, most notable for his science fiction writing. anderson was born in london, england, on 21 april 1882. he died on 9 may 1969. anderson's first published story, "the merman's wife", was published in the magazine " pulp" in 1912. he became well-known as a science fiction author in the 1930s, with such novels as "the war of the worlds" (1938), "ender's game" (1968), and "the andromeda strain" (1971). his work often explores the potential consequences of technological advancement, and has been seen as influential in the
the junior presidents cup is a junior world golf championship contested by amateur golfers under the age of 18. held annually since 1968, it is the only junior world golf championship played outside of the major championships. the first junior presidents cup was contested in 1968 at the royal liverpool golf club in england. the event was conceived by the united states golf association (usga) and organized by english golf officials. the inaugural event was won by american stewart cink, who was then 14 years old. the junior presidents cup is currently sponsored by american express and is played at
antonietta meneghel (27 june 189326 january 1975), better known by her stage name totò, was an italian singer, actor, comedian and film director. born in naples, totò began his performing career in the 1920s as a singer and comedian in local theaters. in 1944 he made his film debut in the film il barbiere di siviglia (the barber of seville), which established him as one of the leading comic actors of the era. he achieved international fame for his performances in the films il deserto rosso (the red desert) and la dolce vita (sweet life), both of which were awarded
theatre of cameroon consists in the theatrical art form that is practiced in cameroon. it has its origins in traditional storytelling, ritual performance and religious ceremonies. the theatre of cameroon has seen a renaissance in recent years, with new productions being created and performances being given in both urban and rural areas. theatre of cameroon can be traced back to traditional storytelling, ritual performance and religious ceremonies. the early tradition of theatre in cameroon was based on the oral tradition, which meant that there was a great deal of variation in the way that theatre was performed across the country.
a historiated initial is an initial, an ornament in the form of a letter, which was used in early modern manuscripts and printed books. they were often based on designs from the heraldic tradition, or from classical antiquity. most historiated initials are small, but some are quite large; the largest known is the great bible of 1539, which features over 500 initials. they were used to add a degree of ornamentation to text, and to help readers more easily identify particular sections or subsections of a book. they were also used as an aid to memory, as readers could more
is a japanese light novel series written by koushi tachibana and illustrated by sora tokui. it was originally published in japanese online magazine "aesthetic" between july 2012 and september 2013, and has been collected into nine volumes. the series follows the story of high school student kurosaki isshiki, who is afflicted with a rare condition that renders him immune to the pain and emotions of others. because of this, isshiki has developed a cynical outlook on life and is content to spend his days alone in his room. however, one day he meets a girl named rin who has also
tropical cyclone alibera was the second longest-lasting tropical cyclone on record, lasting for 34 days. alibera originated from a low pressure area over the indian ocean on october 10, 2004. the system intensified into a tropical storm on october 12 and quickly attained hurricane status. alibera reached its peak intensity with winds of 165 mph (270 km/h) on october 16 before weakening due to unfavorable conditions. the storm made landfall in southern india on october 18, subsequently dissipating the next day. alibera was a significant storm due to its long duration and high winds. the storm caused extensive damage throughout
the dixieland jug blowers were a popular ensemble of jug players who flourished in new orleans during the late 1800s and early 1900s. the group is best known for its lively performances of traditional new orleans jazz tunes, which often featured complex improvisations on the jug. the dixieland jug blowers were formed in the 1890s by african americans who had migrated from the south to new orleans. the group was initially composed of four jugglers: pete ladner, fred waite, paul barbarin, and joe morris. over the years, other members were added, including clarinetist sidney bechet and trombonist kid ory. the
a biointerface is the region of contact between two or more biological systems, where the components of one system interact with the components of the other system. biointerfaces can be found in all types of biological systems, from cells to tissues to organs. biointerfaces are important because they allow communication between different parts of a biological system. they also play an important role in the regulation and function of these systems. biointerfaces can be found in both normal and abnormal tissue, and have been implicated in a variety of diseases. the biointerface research field is growing rapidly, and there is
gerard joseph britton (born 20 october 1970) is an english former professional footballer who played as a midfielder. he made over 300 appearances in the premier league and football league, most notably for burnley and watford. britton represented england at under-21 level. born in liverpool, britton began his career with local side everton before joining burnley for £650,000 in 1992. he spent six seasons at turf moor, making over 220 appearances, before moving to watford for £1.5 million in 1998. britton helped watford to promotion to the premier league in 2000–01, and also won the fa cup in 2002. he
charles r. harding (aka ‘wag’ harding) (c.1866-1941) was an american astronomer who made significant contributions to the field of astrophysics. he is best known for his work on the structure and evolution of stars and galaxies, as well as his investigations into the nature of light. harding was born in 1866 in easton, massachusetts. after completing his undergraduate studies at amherst college in 1887, he began graduate studies at harvard university, where he received his doctorate in 1893. he subsequently became a faculty member at harvard, where he remained for the rest of his career. harding made significant contributions to
pampulha (portuguese: região administrativa da pampulha) is a metropolitan area located in the brazilian state of minas gerais. it is the most populous municipality of the region, with a population of 1,827,451 in 2009. the region has a population density of 1,700 inhabitants per square kilometer. the region is bordered by the city of belo horizonte to the north, the municipalities of montes claros and governador valadares to the east, the municipality of araxá to the south, and the state of espírito santo to the west. the region has a total area of 319 square kilometers. the region was created
on november 15, 1984, when belo horizonte divided its metropolitan area into pampulha and campinas regions. the region has experienced significant economic growth since its creation; in 2009 it had a gdp of r$ 113 billion (us$ 34 billion). the main economic activities are services (74%), industry (15%), and agriculture (7%). the region has two universities: universidade federal de minas gerais (ufmg) and universidade estadual de campinas (unicamp). the region is home to several attractions, including the pampulha observatory, which is one of brazil's most important astronomical observatories; são lourenço mine, one of brazil's largest gold mines; and itaipu dam,
norway proper as a geographic term in norway basically refers to the area west of the oslofjord, north of trondheim and east of the sognefjord. it comprises roughly two-thirds of the country. norway proper is a large and sparsely populated region, with a population density of just over 100 people per square kilometer. the region has a largely rural character, with few large towns or cities. the region is dominated by mountains and forests, with a coastline along the north sea. the region is home to a number of important cultural and historical sites, including the medieval city of bergen,
mission china is a 2017 indian assamese-language drama film directed by rupesh sarma and produced by p.k. bora. the film stars arun chhetri, sonam kapoor, siddharth narayan and tapas paul in lead roles. the film is set in the fictional town of dili in arunachal pradesh, during the 1962 sino-indian war. it tells the story of a group of young people who are forced to flee their homes after chinese troops invade the town. they journey through the forest to india, and eventually settle in calcutta. development on the project began in 2013, when sarma met producer bora while shooting
an episode of the television series "crime story". bora agreed to produce the film on condition that sarma direct it. the cast was announced in january 2017, with chhetri and kapoor being cast as the lead characters. filming began in may 2017 and ended in august. mission china premiered at the 43rd international film festival of india in january 2018, where it received positive reviews from critics. the film was released in india on 25 january 2018 and was also screened at the berlin international film festival, where it won the silver bear for best feature film. it has been
andy bronkema (born february 23, 1984) is an american musician and songwriter. he is best known as the lead vocalist, guitarist and principal songwriter for the post-hardcore band chiodos. born in des moines, iowa, bronkema moved to nashville, tennessee at the age of thirteen to pursue a music career. he formed the band chiodos in 2001 with drummer brett gurewitz, bassist jesse shatkin and guitarist derrick plourde. the band released their debut album, room to breathe, in 2002 on epitaph records. the album received critical acclaim, and the singles "pass out" and "no one really loves you" became major hits
on college radio. the band toured extensively throughout 2002 and 2003 in support of room to breathe, playing alongside bands such as all that remains, a static lullaby and saves the day. bronkema left chiodos in 2003 to focus on his solo career. he released his first solo album, a good night to die, in 2004 on epitaph records. the album was met with mixed reviews but did well commercially. bronkema toured heavily in support of the album, playing alongside bands such as fall out boy and my chemical romance. bronkema rejoined chiodos in 2006 after gurewitz left the band.
manuel ramos otero (july 20, 1948 – march 3, 2010) was a mexican politician and lawyer who served as the governor of the state of tamaulipas from january 1, 1998 to december 31, 2004. ramos otero was born in matamoros, tamaulipas, on july 20, 1948. he studied law at the national autonomous university of mexico (unam), where he graduated with a degree in law in 1971. after completing his legal studies, ramos otero worked as a lawyer in matamoros. in 1987, ramos otero was elected to the mexican congress as a member of the institutional revolutionary party (pri). he served
richard duncan fraser (ca. 1784 – april 21, 1855) was a nineteenth-century canadian jurist and legislator. born in amherst, nova scotia, fraser was the son of duncan fraser and margaret mcnab. he was educated at the pictou academy and the law school of dalhousie university in halifax. he was called to the nova scotia bar in 1811 and practiced law in amherst. in 1820, fraser was elected to the nova scotia house of assembly as a tory. he served as speaker of the house from 1830 to 1834. in 1838, he was appointed to the privy council of canada. in
six flags dubai was a planned theme park that was to be built on a reclaimed area of dubai's coastline. the park was announced in february 2010, and construction began the following year. the park was originally scheduled to open in the summer of 2012, but delays in obtaining permits and the global financial crisis caused the project to be cancelled. six flags dubai was to be built on a reclaimed area of dubai's coastline, located between jumeirah beach park and the dubai marine park. the park was announced in february 2010, and construction began the following year. the park
was originally scheduled to open in the summer of 2012, but delays in obtaining permits and the global financial crisis caused the project to be cancelled. the park was planned to feature six themed areas: an adventure park, a water park, a family entertainment area, a coaster, a medieval-themed area, and a themed village. the adventure park would have included a log flume ride, an ice rink, and an airplane simulator ride. the water park would have featured three theme pools, a wave pool, and a kids' water play area. the family entertainment area would have included a large roller
"when october goes" is a ballad based on a true story. the song was written by american singer-songwriter taylor swift and british singer ed sheeran. it was released as the fourth and final single from swift's fifth studio album, "reputation" (2018). the song is a departure from the pop rock sound of "reputation" and features a more subdued production, withstrings and pianos replacing the synthesizers and drum machines of her previous releases. the lyrics are written about the end of a relationship, with swift singing about how october "goes to show" that the person she loved is gone. "when october
goes" debuted at number 73 on the us "billboard" hot 100 chart before climbing to number 41 in its fifth week. it became her fourth top 40 hit on the chart, following "i don't wanna live forever" (2017), "look what you made me do" (2017) and "shape of you" (2017). in canada, the song peaked at number 16 on the canadian hot 100 chart. the song has been praised by music critics for its emotional depth and lyrical quality. it was nominated for best pop duo/group performance at the 61st annual grammy awards, but lost to sheeran and nancy wilson
sch (an abbreviation for "schizophrenia") is the fourth album by the norwegian rock band, a-ha. released in 1984, it was their first album with new frontman morten harket. the album was a departure from the band's earlier pop music, and contained heavier elements of rock and electronic music. it reached number one on the norwegian charts and became their most successful album. "sch" has been certified platinum in norway. sch is considered a-ha's breakthrough album, and influenced the development of norwegian rock in the late 1980s. the album has been praised for its complex songwriting and harket's distinctive vocals. it
starcom21 is a statewide public safety trunked radio system serving new york state. it is the primary public safety radio network in the state, and is operated by the new york state police. the system began operations in 1984 as a joint project of the new york state police and the federal communications commission. at its inception, starcom21 consisted of a limited number of channels covering only parts of new york city. over time, the system has expanded to cover most of the state. as of 2009, the system had a total of 1,878 active users. starcom21 is a trunked
gdut uavs are chinese uavs developed by the gdut corporation. the company is a subsidiary of the china aerospace science and technology corporation. the gdut uavs are designed for military and commercial applications, such as mapping, surveying, mapping photography, aerial cinematography, and providing real-time intelligence. some of the notable features of gdut uavs include: -high altitude capability: the gdut uav can operate at an altitude of up to 4,000 meters. this makes them well-suited for applications such as mapping and surveying. -fast flight speed: the gdut uavs can fly at a speed of up to 150 kilometers per hour. this
stuart b. mciver (1921–2008) was a historian and writer who specialized in the history of the american west. he is best known for his book the west of john ford, which won the los angeles times book prize in 1976. stuart mciver was born in 1921 in waco, texas. after graduating from high school, he attended baylor university for two years, but left to serve in world war ii. after the war, he returned to baylor and completed his undergraduate degree in 1948. he then went to the university of california, berkeley, where he received his doctorate in history in
1954. after receiving his doctorate, mciver taught at several universities before joining the faculty at san diego state university as an associate professor in 1964. he became a full professor there in 1967 and remained there until his retirement in 1998. mciver's career as a historian focused largely on the history of the american west. his books include the west of john ford (1976), the great plains (1978), and the far west (1983). he also wrote articles for various journals and magazines, and was twice nominated for a pulitzer prize. stuart mciver died on december 31, 2008 at the age
the tailhook scandal was a military scandal that involved the sexual molestation of women by american military personnel at the 1986 tailhook association convention in las vegas. the scandal began to come to light in november 2011, when a retired navy captain who had been involved in the scandal published an article in the san diego union-tribune. in january 2012, the naval criminal investigative service opened an investigation into the affair. in march 2012, seven active duty servicemen were charged with crimes ranging from sexual assault to adultery. on 12 may 2012, lieutenant general william boykin, the former deputy director
katy sexton, mbe (born 21 july 1981) is an english actress. she is known for her role as lucy beech in the bbc soap opera eastenders, for which she won the british soap awards best actress award in 2006 and 2007. sexton was born in ilford, essex, england, to a mother who worked as a psychiatric nurse and a father who was a carpenter. she has two sisters. sexton attended ilford county high school for girls. sexton trained at the central school of speech and drama, graduating in 2005. sexton made her television debut in 2002 with a role in
the drama series young james. in 2003, she appeared in the bbc soap opera eastenders as lucy beech. sexton left eastenders in 2006 to pursue other acting opportunities. since leaving eastenders, sexton has appeared in a number of films and television shows. in 2007, she starred in the film the boat that rocked as peggy ashcroft and received critical acclaim for her performance. that same year, she won the british soap awards best actress award for her role as lucy beech on eastenders. she also appeared in the 2008 film stardust as rachel truefitt and the 2009 film red riding
huseyn javid monument is a monument in tehran, iran, commemorating the iranian politician and statesman huseyn javid. the monument is located in the center of tehran, on the north side of the taleghani boulevard. the monument was designed by iranian architect sadeq khosrowshahi and completed in 1984. it is made of marble and granite, and stands high. the monument features a statue of javid, with a bas-relief of his political achievements carved on its front. the inscription on the monument reads: "huseyn javid, son of hajji hashem, was born in tehran in 1881. he died in tehran on 12 may
bulletproof is a british police procedural series, created by jason haigh-ellery and produced by kudos productions for the bbc. it is set in a fictional police force, the north yorkshire police, in the north of england. the series follows the investigations of detective superintendent david riggs and his team, as they attempt to solve complex crimes. the show is written by haigh-ellery and directed by jamie doran. bulletproof has been generally well received by critics, who praised its writing and cast. it has been nominated for several awards, including a bafta award for best drama series and a golden globe
the national museum of liberia is a national museum in monrovia, liberia. it was founded in 1968, and is dedicated to the history of liberia and its people. the museum has a collection of artifacts from across liberia and from around the world. the museum also has an art gallery. the national museum of liberia is located in central monrovia, at the junction of independence avenue and church street. it is next to the national palace, which is now used as the headquarters of the liberian government. the museum is open daily from 9am to 5pm. admission is free. the
mount blum, or mount bald, is a mountain in the san bernardino national forest, east of the city of san bernardino in southern california. at an elevation of 10,853 feet (3,302 meters), it is the highest peak in the san bernardino mountains. mount blum is one of the many peaks in the range that form a watershed for the santa ana river. the mountain drains southward into the santa ana river and northeastward into the san gabriel river. the peak forms part of the eastern boundary of the cleveland national forest. the mountain was named after bernard blum, a geologist
sabreen hisbani is a pakistani television actress and model. sabreen hisbani was born in karachi, sindh, pakistan on 25 january 1990. she completed her early education from bolan school in karachi. after completing her education, sabreen started modelling and acting in commercials and television serials. in 2009, she made her acting debut with the drama serial "tum se hi". later that year she starred in the mystery thriller series "dilwale" as mahira khan's love interest, aamir. in 2011, sabreen played a pivotal role in the drama serial "tera zindagi" as zoya, a young girl who falls in love with farooq
(played by imran abbas). in 2012, sabreen played a supporting role as komal in the romantic drama series "tum se hi pyar ka". in 2013, sabreen starred alongside humayun saeed and aamina sheikh in the comedy-drama series "tere naam". the series was produced by humayun saeed's company hum television. in 2014, sabreen starred alongside hamza ali abbasi and shehzad sheikh in the family comedy-drama series "qubool hai". the series was produced by hum television and aired on geo tv. in 2015, sabreen starred alongside imran abbas and reham khan in the romantic drama series "tera mera saath". the series was
ali muhsin al-barwani (13 january 1919 in baghdad, iraq – 21 october 1992 in baghdad, iraq) was an iraqi scholar and educationalist. al-barwani was born on 13 january 1919 in baghdad, iraq. he received his early education at the al-zahra school in baghdad and then continued his studies at the american university of beirut where he earned his bachelor's degree in 1940. he then returned to baghdad to complete his graduate studies at the university of baghdad, where he earned his doctorate in 1953. al-barwani began his career as a teacher and administrator at the al-najaf university in najaf, iraq.
he served as the dean of the university's faculty of education from 1962 until 1970. in 1970 he was appointed president of baghdad university, a position he held until his death in 1992. al-barwani was a prolific scholar and author. his publications include books on education and pedagogy, as well as articles on various subjects including philosophy, literature, and history. he is also credited with being the founder of modern iraqi education reform. ali muhsin al-barwani was a leading figure in iraqi education for more than four decades. he played a pivotal role in transforming iraqi education from an archaic
blood is blood is a 2016 horror film written and directed by s. craig zahler. the film stars patrick stewart, boyd holbrook, and trevante rhodes. after a group of college students are viciously killed in a sorority house, the killer assumes the identity of one of the dead girls and begins stalking the remaining survivors. as the bodies pile up, the survivors start to fear for their lives - until they realize that the killer is after them specifically. now they must use all their ingenuity and courage to outwit their killer before he finally claims their blood as his
desol is the first major album release by the american rock band desol. the album was released on september 26, 2009 through vagrant records. desol is an american rock band from los angeles, california. formed in 2006, the band consists of vocalist and guitarist justin furstenfeld, bassist and backing vocalist jack perrin, and drummer will schlesinger. the band's debut album, "desol", was released on vagrant records on september 26, 2009. the album was produced by furstenfeld and recorded at the parlour studios in hollywood, california with producer john feldmann. it was preceded by the single "saving my life" which charted
