zofia posmysz-piasecka (; born 23 august 1923) is a polish composer, conductor, and pianist. born in warsaw, posmysz studied at the warsaw conservatory, where she was a pupil of witold lutosławski and stefan witos. she made her conducting debut in 1952 with the polish national opera. she has worked as a conductor with many ensembles, including the berlin philharmonic, royal philharmonic orchestra, los angeles philharmonic, london symphony orchestra, and polish radio symphony orchestra. she has also served as the music director of the warsaw philharmonic (1965-1975), orchestre de paris (1976-1977), and royal danish opera (1977-1981). in 1981 she was appointed
ernest bernard malley (; 26 may 1897 – 9 december 1975), also known as ernie o'malley, was an irish american writer and journalist. he is best known for his novel, the mayor of coney island (1942), which tells the story of a jewish immigrant who becomes the democratic party mayor of coney island in the 1930s. ernest bernard malley was born in county clare, ireland on 26 may 1897. he moved to the united states with his family in 1905. malley attended boston college and columbia university, but dropped out after a year to become a journalist. in 1922, he
melbourne hall is a georgian country house located in the civil parish of wotton-under-edge, gloucestershire, england. it was built in 1770 for the banker and politician john robinson and is a grade ii* listed building. the house was originally built on the site of an earlier tudor hall and was enlarged by george robinson, nephew of john robinson, in about 1825. the house passed through several hands before becoming a school in the 1930s. it became a hotel in the 1970s and was bought by the national trust in 1984. the house is open to the public and has a
the tree of patriarchy is a metaphor used by feminists to describe the patriarchal system of society. the metaphor suggests that the tree is a structure with many branches and roots, with the branches representing different aspects of society and the roots representing the patriarchy. the tree of patriarchy is a metaphor used by feminists to describe the patriarchal system of society. the metaphor suggests that the tree is a structure with many branches and roots, with the branches representing different aspects of society and the roots representing the patriarchy. the tree can be seen as a structure that supports
carijoa riisei, the snowflake coral or branched coral, is a species of coral in the family merulinidae. it is found on the western coast of north america from central california to baja california, and in the eastern pacific ocean from ecuador to peru. carijoa riisei is a branching coral that can grow to a height of about . it has a uniform, pale pink or white surface, with small black spots. the coral has short branches that are arranged in whorls. the coral is fast-growing and can spread rapidly by growing new branches from the existing ones. carijoa riisei is
wilhelm cauer (24 june 1900 – 22 december 1992) was an austrian mathematician who made significant contributions to algebra and analytic geometry. born in vienna, cauer studied at the university of vienna and the university of munich, obtaining his doctorate from the latter in 1926. he became a privatdozent at the university of vienna in 1929, and a full professor there in 1942. in 1945 he moved to the university of california, berkeley, where he remained until his retirement in 1968. cauer is best known for his work on algebra and analytic geometry, which includes the development of cauer's theorem
and cauer's principle. he also made significant contributions to differential geometry, including the cauchy–riemann hypothesis. he was elected to the national academy of sciences in 1970. wilhelm cauer was born on 24 june 1900 in vienna, austria, to georg cauer and margarethe (née kugler). he showed an early aptitude for mathematics and studied at the university of vienna under max dehn and ludwig boltzmann, obtaining his doctorate in 1926. after post-doctoral study at the university of munich under rudolf peierls he became a privatdozent at the university of vienna in 1929. in 1942 he moved to the university of california,
the seventh season of the bleach anime series premiered on october 3, 2016 and concluded on december 21, 2016. after defeating yhwach, ichigo and his allies are now looking to rebuild their lives. however, when a new threat appears, they must band together once more to protect their loved ones. the seventh season of the anime series premiered on october 3, 2016 and concluded on december 21, 2016. it is directed by kenji shimizu and written by toshimichi kameda. the series features the return of tite kubo as the creator and director and yūichi nakamura as the original character designer.
harold leland yochum (june 7, 1903 - may 30, 1987) was an american microbiologist who won the nobel prize in physiology or medicine in 1966. harold l. yochum was born on june 7, 1903, in salt lake city, utah. he received his undergraduate degree from the university of utah in 1925 and his ph.d. from yale university in 1930. yochum began his career as a research scientist at the national institutes of health in bethesda, maryland, where he worked for more than thirty years. in 1962 he became the first director of the institute for medical research and development at
i love bacon! is a cookbook with over 120 recipes that include bacon in some form. whether it's in a savory dish like a bacon-wrapped dates stuffed with goat cheese or a sweet dish like bacon-wrapped strawberries, there is something for everyone in this cookbook. i love bacon! was created by two friends who love bacon and wanted to share their love with the world. the recipes were all tested and perfected over time by the authors, who are both cooks and bacon lovers. whether you're new to bacon or a bacon connoisseur, i love bacon! has something for you.
dwight marcy (june 8, 1840 – may 28, 1912) was an american astronomer and author. he is best known for his discovery of the marcy–leverrier effect in 1881. born on june 8, 1840 in the town of northbridge, massachusetts, dwight marcy was educated at phillips academy and then at yale university where he received his a.b. in 1861 and his a.m. in 1863. after a year of teaching at the lawrence scientific school in harvard university, he served as an observer on the u.s. naval observatory from 1865 to 1868, during which time he made several notable discoveries, including the
luka nižetić (born 12 august 1983) is a serbian professional footballer who plays as a striker for belgian club kortrijk. nižetić started his career in his home town club ofk beograd. he then moved to fk rad in the serbian first league, and finished the season with 16 goals in 27 matches. he then moved to dutch side sc heerenveen, where he made his debut on 25 august 2003 in a 2–1 home win against psv eindhoven. nižetić scored 10 goals in 33 league matches for heerenveen before moving to spanish club valencia in the summer of 2006 for €5
million. in his debut season with valencia he scored 21 goals in all competitions, helping valencia to fourth place in la liga. in 2009, he joined premier league side liverpool for £16 million. nižetić made his liverpool debut on 23 october 2009 against wigan athletic, coming on as a substitute for fernando torres in the 73rd minute. nižetić's first goal for liverpool was an 83rd-minute penalty against everton on 1 december 2009, which secured a 2–0 victory. on 4 february 2011, nižetić scored the winning goal against manchester united at anfield, giving liverpool their first premier league title since 1990.
roy neil ferguson, , is the former president and ceo of pepsico. he served in this role from january 1, 2007 until his resignation on november 7, 2014. ferguson was born in queens, new york, and raised in the outer boroughs of new york city. he is a graduate of the university of california, berkeley with a degree in business administration. ferguson began his career as an investment banker at arthur andersen. he then worked for mckinsey & company before joining pepsico in 1992 as a product manager. he became president and ceo of pepsico in 2007. under ferguson's leadership,
pepsico made substantial investments in new products and brands, such as frito-lay's lay's potato chips, quaker oats' granola bars, tropicana orange juice and gatorade sports drinks. the company also acquired several food companies, including dunkin' donuts and burger king. in 2013, pepsico announced that it plans to purchase mondelez international for $23 billion. ferguson has been involved with a number of philanthropic organizations, including the clinton global initiative and the united way. he is also a member of the board of directors for the ymca of metropolitan new york. he is married to actress nene leakes and they have two
