was the pen-name of japanese author viscount inoue kinoshita (1867-1944). he was born into an aristocratic family and studied in europe before returning to japan in 1898. he began writing novels in the early 20th century, and is considered one of the leading figures of the modern japanese novel. kinoshita rigen is considered one of the leading figures of the modern japanese novel. his novels explore themes such as class structure, political corruption, and love affairs. kinoshita is also known for his psychological realism, which is evident in his depictions of characters emotions and motivations. kinoshita was born into an
kevin patrick shields (born 21 may 1963) is an english musician, songwriter, and producer who is best known as the founder, guitarist, and main songwriter of the alternative rock band radiohead. shields was born in reading, berkshire, england. he attended abingdon school and studied at the university of exeter. he first came to prominence as the guitarist and main songwriter for the post-punk band the cure. after the cure disbanded in 1987, shields formed radiohead with his brother jonathan and drummer philip selway. the band's debut album, pablo honey (1993), drew critical acclaim and established radiohead as one of the
loops of fury is an extended play by american metalcore band as i lay dying. it was released on june 23, 2016 through metal blade records. the ep was recorded at audiohammer studios in sanford, florida with producer chris collin and features guest appearances from vocalist tim lambesis of arch enemy and guitarist phil anselmo of pantera. loops of fury is an extended play by american metalcore band as i lay dying. it was released on june 23, 2016 through metal blade records. the ep was recorded at audiohammer studios in sanford, florida with producer chris collin and features guest
appearances from vocalist tim lambesis of arch enemy and guitarist phil anselmo of pantera. the ep is the first new material from the band since the release of their fifth album, "the end of days", in 2013. it was preceded by the release of the single "lies my lover told me" on april 28, 2016. loops of fury contains five tracks lasting a total length of 31 minutes and 38 seconds. the title track is a seven-and-a-half-minute long song that features heavy usage of guitars solos and drum double-bass drumming, while "in memory of" is a seven-minute long ballad that
is a survival horror game for the playstation vita, developed by drinkbox studios and published by sony interactive entertainment europe. the game was announced at the playstation media showcase at paris games week on september 7, 2013, and was released in october 2013. the game is set in a post-apocalyptic world where vampires have taken over and humanity is on the brink of extinction. the protagonist must use their wits and skills to survive against the undead while trying to find a way to stop the vampire count. "countdown vampires" received mixed reviews from critics. it has a metacritic score
an inhaler (also known as a puffer, nebulizer, or spacer) is a medical device that uses compressed gas to deliver medication into the lungs. it is typically used to treat breathing problems such as asthma, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (copd), and cystic fibrosis. inhalers are also used in pediatric pulmonology to treat conditions such as wheezing caused by allergies or asthma. the inhaler consists of an airtight, often plastic, container with a mouthpiece at one end and a nebulizer at the other. the container is filled with a compressed gas, such as helium, and the user breathes in deeply through
the house of savoy-carignano originated as the savoyard branch of the house of carignano. the family acquired its name from the castle of carignano, which they occupied from the 11th century. the first member of the house to achieve prominence was amadeus i, count of savoy, who in 1162 became count of montferrat and moved his court to carignano. his descendants, the savoys, ruled until 1860. the dynasty reached its zenith under victor emmanuel ii, who was king of italy from 1848 to 1861. in 1861, he became king of sardinia and naples as well as duke of savoy and
prince of piedmont-sardinia. he then added the title of grand duke of tuscany to his other titles. under his rule, the house of savoy became one of the most powerful royal families in europe. however, during the latter part of victor emmanuel's reign, tensions arose between him and his various ministers. this led to a series of political crises known as the five days of milan (1859), which ultimately led to his abdication. following victor emmanuel's abdication, the house of savoy was abolished by a decree of the italian parliament on december 12, 1860. however, a few members of the
uss indiana (bb-58) was the second of the two indiana-class battleships of the united states navy. she was launched on 20 may 1941, sponsored by mrs. james b. duke, and commissioned on 16 november 1941, with captain george f. elliott in command. following shakedown and training in the caribbean and along the east coast, indiana departed norfolk, virginia, on 3 january 1942, to join the pacific fleet. she transited the panama canal on 9 january and arrived in pearl harbor on 21 january. after a month of training and organization in hawaiian waters, she sailed for the southwest pacific area,
arriving at nouméa, new caledonia, on 4 march 1942. in april and may 1942 she participated in the first american naval offensive of world war ii - the battle of the coral sea - escorting aircraft carriers from pearl harbor to strike at japanese installations on henderson field on new guinea. in june she joined admiral chester w. nimitz's pacific fleet at midway and participated in the battle of midway (4-7 june) as part of task force 16 under admiral raymond a. spruance. after a two-day bombardment of midway island by her guns, she bombarded kavieng, new ireland (14-15 june),
canal 6 (alternately known as multimedios televisión) is a mexican television network that is owned by the grupo televisa. it is one of the oldest television networks in mexico. canal 6 was founded on september 5, 1958, as a cultural channel, broadcasting programs from movie theaters and art galleries. in 1970, it became a general entertainment channel. in the early 1990s, it began to specialize in telenovelas. in 2000, it became a 24-hour network. canal 6 is available throughout mexico and in the united states through telemundo. since its inception, canal 6 has been the home of some of mexico's
ladislav haškovec (may 18, 1866 – january 26, 1936) was a slovak violinist and composer. haškovec was born in liptovský mikuláš, then part of the austro-hungarian empire. he studied at the vienna academy of music with joseph joachim and joseph haydn. in 1895 he won the first prize in the paris conservatoire competition. after his debut in 1894 at the gewandhaus in leipzig he toured europe extensively, appearing in vienna, budapest, prague, berlin, milan, barcelona and many other cities. he became a professor at the prague conservatory (1910-1936) and at the university of music and performing arts vienna (1920-1936). haškovec
