theodore cyrus karp (17 july 1926 – 5 april 2010) was an american mathematician and computer scientist. karp was born in new york city, and attended the city college of new york, where he received his b.a. in 1947. he then attended the university of wisconsin–madison, where he received his m.a. in 1948 and his ph.d. in 1951, both under the supervision of john von neumann. karp was a professor at princeton university from 1951 to 1966, when he became a professor at the institute for advanced study in princeton, new jersey. he retired from princeton in 1998, and died
super bowl xxvi was an american football game between the national football conference (nfc) champion san francisco 49ers and the american football conference (afc) champion denver broncos to determine the nfl champion for the 1990 season. the 49ers defeated the broncos by the score of 49–33. the game was played on january 30, 1991, at candlestick park in san francisco. it was the first super bowl played in california and the last to be played at candlestick park. the 49ers entered the game as favorites, as they had won both their regular season games and finished first in their division.
ningxia (, ; alternately romanized as ningsia, ningxia hui, or hui ningxia) is a province of the people's republic of china. located in the northwest of the country, it borders gansu and shaanxi provinces to the west, inner mongolia and xinjiang uyghur autonomous region to the north, and mongolia to the east. with a population of more than 23 million as of 2010, it is the most populous province in china by far. the provincial capital is lanzhou. ningxia is renowned for its natural resources, including oil and coal. the province has been expanding rapidly into an industrial center, with
the sweetest mango is a 2001 romantic comedy film directed by sri lankan-born australian filmmaker wm. jayasuriya and written by australian american screenwriter suzan-lori parks. the sweetest mango is a story of a young woman, neela (nirupa roy), who falls in love with an american man, matt (tony goldwyn), while working as a nanny in his family home in melbourne, australia. neela is initially skeptical of matt's intentions towards her, but the two eventually fall in love and marry. however, when neela discovers that matt is actually a millionaire, she is forced to confront the reality of her new life
the epistle of jude, often shortened to jude, is a book of the new testament. it is traditionally attributed to jude, the brother of jesus, and written between 62 and 65 ad. the epistle of jude is a brief letter, only 29 verses long, but it has a profound impact on christian faith and theology. in it, jude warns believers against false teachings that had crept into the early church and threatened its foundations. these teachings included gnosticism, which taught that salvation came not through faith in jesus christ but through secret knowledge and understanding. jude also urges believers to
a long firm fraud (also known as a ponzi scheme or a pyramid scheme) is a type of fraudulent business practice in which a person or group of people promises investors high returns on their investment, usually through the sale of shares in a new business venture. the returns are typically paid from the contributions of new investors, rather than from the profits of the business itself. the long firm fraud is one of the most common types of fraud, and is also one of the most difficult to detect and prosecute. the schemes usually involve a small number of
