the devil's jumps are a series of hills in the english county of devon, located between the towns of barnstaple and ilfracombe. the name is derived from the old english deofol's jumpe meaning "the leap of the devil". the hills are a popular spot for walkers and cyclists, and are also known for their views. the devil's jumps are a series of hills in the english county of devon, located between the towns of barnstaple and ilfracombe. the name is derived from the old english deofol's jumpe meaning "the leap of the devil". the hills are a popular spot for
