dan meyer (born april 7, 1957) is an american comedian and television personality. he is best known for his work on the sketch comedy series saturday night live from 1985 to 1990, as well as his work on the 1990s sitcom the new adventures of old christine. meyer was also a regular performer on the game show deal or no deal from 2004 to 2007. meyer was born in ithaca, new york, and grew up in bethlehem, pennsylvania. he is jewish. meyer studied at the university of michigan before moving to new york city to pursue a career in comedy.
he began working as a writer and performer for saturday night live in 1985, and became a cast member the following year. meyer left snl in 1990 to focus on his new sitcom, the new adventures of old christine. the show ran for six seasons and was later adapted into an nbc television series that ran from 2006 to 2009. meyer has since starred in two short-lived sitcoms: dan meyer's world in 2001 and the dan meyer project in 2002. in 2006, he joined the cast of the game show deal or no deal as a regular player; he remained
swissair flight 111 was a scheduled international passenger flight from geneva, switzerland to new york city. on 11 september 2001, the aircraft, a mcdonnell douglas dc-10-30, crashed into the north atlantic off the coast of nova scotia, canada while en route to new york city with 227 passengers and crew aboard. the crash was the deadliest in swissair history and remains the deadliest aviation disaster in north american history. the aircraft was operating on a scheduled passenger flight with a planned stop in new york city. at approximately 10:47 am edt, swissair flight 111 lost contact with air traffic control,
the tortworth chestnut is an ancient sweet chestnut tree that is located in the tortworth valley in the english county of hampshire. the tree is believed to be over 1,000 years old and is the largest sweet chestnut tree in the world. the tortworth chestnut is a large, ancient sweet chestnut tree that is located in the tortworth valley in the english county of hampshire. the tree is believed to be over 1,000 years old and is the largest sweet chestnut tree in the world. the tortworth chestnut is a popular tourist destination due to its size and historical significance.
demining or mine clearance is the process of detecting and disposing of land mines and improvised explosive devices. demining is often carried out by demining experts, military personnel, or civilians using specialised equipment. the land mine problem has been ongoing since the end of world war i. by the end of world war ii, over two million people had been killed or wounded by land mines, amounting to an estimated total of over 20 million casualties. the number of casualties since then has continued to increase, with an estimated total of over 70 million casualties since world war ii. the
on 20 june 1789, the members of the national assembly in paris, france, came together to draft the declaration of the rights of man and of the citizen. one of the provisions in this document was the tennis court oath, which stated that "no member of the national assembly shall swear any other oath than this: i swear by god the father, and by the honor and dignity of the national assembly, to fulfill faithfully my duties as a member thereof." the tennis court oath was a pledge made by members of the national assembly in paris, france, in 1789.
richard s. "rick" clayburgh (born april 8, 1955) is an american actor and musician. he is best known for his role as deputy sheriff jesse pinkman on the amc television series the walking dead. clayburgh was born in 1955 in houston, texas, the son of bettye (née duffy), a homemaker, and richard clayburgh sr., an advertising executive. he has two sisters. clayburgh moved to los angeles with his family when he was 10 years old, and began his acting career at the age of 12, appearing in tv commercials. in 1978, clayburgh made his feature film debut in the cult
otto adolf eichmann ( , ; 19 october 1906 – 11 may 1962) was an austrian-born nazi ss officer who was responsible for the deportation of millions of jews to concentration and extermination camps during the holocaust. he was found guilty of war crimes and crimes against humanity at the 1961 trial of the eichmann trial, and executed by israel in 1962. born in austria, eichmann worked as a gestapo officer in vienna and later in prague, where he helped to organize the nazi administration of czechoslovakia. in 1941, he was transferred to berlin, where he became head of the
jewish division of the gestapo. he played a central role in the implementation of the final solution, the nazis' plan to exterminate all jews in europe. in 1942, he was appointed head of the central office for jewish emigration, which coordinated the deportation of jews to concentration and extermination camps in occupied europe. eichmann was captured by israeli forces in may 1945 and initially held at a detention center near tel aviv. he was then transferred to italy and tried by a military tribunal at nuremberg; he was found guilty of war crimes and crimes against humanity and sentenced to
"sunshine days" is the eighteenth and penultimate studio album by american rock band the beach boys, released on october 27, 1978. it is the group's first album of new material in five years, and their first release on their new label, brother records. the album was recorded at sunset sound recorders in hollywood, california during 1977 and 1978, and produced by the band themselves. the album was well received by critics and achieved modest commercial success, reaching number fourteen on the "billboard" 200 chart. it was certified gold by the recording industry association of america (riaa) on march 2, 1979.
"sunshine days" was written and composed primarily by dennis wilson with additional writing from mike love and al jardine. it is a folk-rock album with influences from country music and soul. the lyrical content focuses on relationships and personal experiences, as well as nostalgia for childhood memories. in 2007, "sunshine days" was remastered and reissued as part of the group's "the beach boys album collection" box set. the set features four cds and one dvd containing extensive liner notes written by music journalist steve turner. a newly mixed stereo version of the album was also included as a disc in
baishan, spanish name cuchillo negro (black knife) is a small town in the huachuca mountains of northern arizona, united states. the population was 1,195 at the 2010 census. baishan was founded in 1888 as a small trading post on the santa cruz river by mormon pioneers who had trekked into the arizona territory in 1881. the post prospered as a supply center for wagon trains heading north to the mining districts of the mogollon rim. in 1907, after a series of devastating floods, the post was relocated to its present site on the banks of the baishan river. the huachuca
conflicting kingdoms is a card-based board game for two to four players, designed by andreas seifert and published by q-workshop. the game is set in the fictional world of arcus, where the monarchs of three rival kingdoms are trying to gain control over the most important regions of the kingdom. players can choose to play as one of the three monarchs, or as one of their rivals. the game is played over a series of rounds, in which each player takes turns playing cards from their hand. on each turn, a player can either play a card to move a
oliver schwerdt (born 13 november 1979) is a german professional racing cyclist, who last rode for uci professional continental team iam cycling. schwerdt has also competed in four editions of the tour de france, his best finish being 19th in 2008. he has also won one stage in the vuelta a españa. schwerdt was born in 1979 in bad neuenahr-ahrweiler, germany. he started cycling at the age of 11, and made his debut as an amateur rider in 1998. he turned professional in 2001 with team csc. schwerdt won one stage of the vuelta a españa, in 2007. he also
tadeusz debski (1921–2011) was a polish survivor of the holocaust and a recipient of the righteous among the nations award. tadeusz debski was born in 1921 in the town of białystok, in the polish province of galicia. he was one of six children of józef and izabela debski. when he was five, the family moved to warsaw, where they settled in żoliborz. debski's father was a tailor and his mother was a seamstress. in 1939, when debski was sixteen, the germans invaded poland and started to round up jews to send to concentration camps. debski's family were quickly taken away
