huntsville rewound is an ongoing non-profit project located in huntsville, alabama, that collects and preserves video, audio, and photo content related to the city's history. huntsville rewound was founded in 2007 by local historian and archivist john t. edge. the project initially focused on collecting video content related to the city's history, but has since expanded its scope to include audio and photo collections as well. the project is funded by donations and sponsorships from local businesses and individuals. huntsville rewound maintains a collection of more than 10,000 videos, 3,000 audio recordings, and 10,000 photos. the project also produces monthly
