paranoid fiction is a term sometimes used to describe fiction in which the protagonist or main character is beset by paranoid delusions or hallucinations. the term is typically used to describe works of speculative fiction, but can also be used to describe works of horror, mystery, or romance. paranoid fiction is a genre that often explores the darker side of human nature. the protagonists of paranoid fiction are often characters who are tormented by their own fears and doubts, and who are often forced to confront the darkness within themselves. these stories often feature intense psychological drama, and often explore
