equine metabolic syndrome (ems), is an endocrinopathy that affects horses, donkeys, and mules. it is a disorder of the metabolism caused by the interactions of several hormones, including insulin, glucagon, and cortisol. ems is one of the most common endocrine disorders in horses and is estimated to affect up to 20% of horses. the condition is characterized by a combination of abnormalities in body weight, blood sugar levels, insulin resistance, and lipid levels. affected horses may experience an increased risk of developing diabetes or other health problems due to their elevated blood sugar levels. diagnosis of ems is based on
