joyful noise is a 2012 american musical drama film written, produced and directed by jonathan demme. the film stars meryl streep, robert de niro, and anne hathaway. joyful noise tells the story of a music teacher (streep) who must come to terms with her past when her daughter (hathaway) decides to start a rock band. demme aimed to create a "generous and affirmative" film that celebrates the power of music. the film premiered at the 2012 toronto international film festival and was released in the united states on september 23, 2012. it received generally positive reviews from critics, who praised
