molecular tagging velocimetry (mtv) is a specific type of volumetric analysis used to study the motion of molecules in fluids. this analysis is particularly useful for studying the dynamics of molecules in gas-liquid and liquid-liquid systems, and can be used to probe the mechanisms of molecular transport. mtv is a versatile technique that can be used to study a wide range of molecular transport phenomena, including diffusion, convection, reaction, and molecular rearrangement. in particular, mtv can be used to probe the role of collisional and non-collisional forces in mediating molecular transport. mtv has been used to study a wide variety
the land of goshen ( or gezer ), sometimes called the land of goshen-gad, is an area in the eastern sinai peninsula. it is bordered on the north by the gulf of aqaba, on the east by the arabian sea, and on the south by israel. the land of goshen was one of the ten provinces of ancient egypt. the province was located in the eastern part of the country, near the mediterranean sea and was divided into three districts: upper (upper) goshen, middle (middle) goshen and lower (lower) goshen. these three districts were further divided into 42 nomes. the
nomes were administrative divisions of ancient egypt. the land of goshen was first mentioned in the egyptian texts known as the ramesside period. it served as one of the provinces of ancient egypt and was located in the eastern part of the country near to the mediterranean sea. the province was divided into three districts: upper (upper) goshen, middle (middle) goshen and lower (lower) goshen. these three districts were further divided into 42 nomes. the nomes were administrative divisions of ancient egypt. the land of goshen was first mentioned in egyptian texts known as the ramesside period. it served as
john dennis carthy (7 april 1923 – 17 december 1997) was an irish folk musician and singer-songwriter. he is best known as the leader of the traditional folk group planxty, which he founded in 1955. carthy was born in dublin, the son of alice (née sweeney), a housewife, and john carthy, a printer and newspaper editor. he studied at trinity college, dublin and at the royal academy of music in london. in 1945 he formed his first group, the dubliners, with his brother tim and two friends from trinity college. the dubliners became one of ireland's most popular folk groups,
touring extensively throughout europe and north america. in 1955 carthy founded planxty with a group of fellow musicians. the band's first album, "the planxty sessions", was released the following year to critical acclaim. carthy's distinctive vocals and guitar playing defined the band's sound, and they went on to release fourteen albums over the next thirty years. in 1987 planxty disbanded; carthy continued to perform solo concerts until his death in 1997. carthy was awarded a cbe in 1988 and a lifetime achievement award from the irish music association in 1996. he was also inducted into the irish music hall of
is the protagonist of gege akutami's manga series "kemono friends". yuta was born in the city of sapporo, hokkaido, japan on february 26th, 1997. at the age of four, yuta's family moves to the suburbs of tokyo. yuta's childhood is filled with a variety of experiences, from playing with friends in the park to helping his parents run the family restaurant. as he gets older, yuta begins to develop an interest in animals, and especially in the furry creatures known as "kemono" (japanese for "beast"). in 2012, at the age of twelve, yuta discovers a website called kemono friends, which
is a virtual reality game based on anthropomorphic animals. excited by this new discovery, yuta spends every free moment he has playing the game. in january 2016, after five years of intensive gameplay and countless hours of exploration, yuta finally completes kemono friends' main story mode. following kemono friends' conclusion, yuta begins to explore other aspects of gaming culture. in february 2017, he creates and posts a video titled "my first time playing an online game with thousands of people." this video quickly becomes one of the most-viewed games-related videos on youtube. in october 2017, yuta releases his first solo
